Working with texts at the second school stage; moving from simple reading towards text comprehension, analysis and interpretation; introduction and creation of  different types of text; finding necessary information for writing texts.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide knowledge and skills to work as a teacher of Estonian on the second stage of primary school.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course a student can apply different strategies of teaching literature, considering the skills as well (special) educational needs of children; can direct the learning process and will know the methodology of teaching Estonian; can arouse interest in different types of text and guide students to create them.
